My very simple effect isn't loading because it appears to have been processed into an .xnb incorrectly. When the effect is loaded, the ContentTypeReaderManager seems to load information about the readers ok but when it gets around to actually reading the content, it's just four or five non-zero bytes and all the rest are zero.  The load operation fails with an ArgumentOutOfRangeException with this call stack:

